"You bring a solid hiking base and gym climbing experience, but Mont Blanc via the Gouter Route demands a significant jump in loaded endurance and altitude-specific fitness. Your biggest gaps are cardio under load and pack-carrying strength — those get the bulk of your training time. As a follower, your climbing training focuses on crampon confidence and glacier comfort rather than leading. Ankle mobility is your weakest flexibility component and critical for crampon technique, so daily mobility work is non-negotiable."